We can rewrite the given expression as
\[\frac{z_3 - z_1}{z_2 - z_1} \cdot \frac{z - z_2}{z - z_3} = \frac{(z_3 - z_1)(z - z_2)}{(z_2 - z_1)(z - z_3)}.\]We want this to be a real number, so the imaginary part of the numerator must be 0.  Expanding, we get
\begin{align*}
&\quad (z_3 - z_1)(z - z_2) \\
&= (78 + 99i - 18 - 83i)(z - 18 - 39i) \\
&= (60 + 16i)(z - 18 - 39i) \\
&= (60z - 1080 - 2340i + 16zi - 288 - 624i + 624i + 1356) \\
&= (60z - 2012 - 1964i + 16zi).
\end{align*}The imaginary part of this expression is $-1964 + 16z,$ so we want $-1964 + 16z = 0.$  Then $z = 123.$

