By the Angle Bisector Theorem, $BD/DC = AB/AC = 17/24$.  Since $BD + DC = BC = 33$, we have $BD = \frac{17}{17 + 24} \cdot 33 = 11$ and $DC = \frac{24}{17 + 24} \cdot 33 = 22$.  Then by the Angle Bisector Theorem again, $BM/MA = BD/DA = 11/22$, so $BM = \frac{11}{11 + 22} \cdot 17 = 5$ and $MA = \frac{22}{11 + 22} \cdot 17 = 12$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.2 cm);

