A = (0,0);
B = (8,0);
C = (2,5);
D = (B + reflect(A,C)*(B))/2;
E = (C + reflect(A,B)*(C))/2;
I = extension(B,D,C,E);
M = (I + reflect(B,C)*(I))/2;
N = (I + reflect(C,B)*(I))/2);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(A--M--N--cycle);
draw(B--D);
draw(C--E);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$D$", D, NE);
label("$E$", E, NW);
label("$I$", I, S);
label("$M$", M, NW);
label("$N$", N, NE);
[/asy]

Similarly, $CN = \frac{24}{17 + 24} \cdot 33 = 21$ and $AN = \frac{17}{17 + 24} \cdot 33 = 12$.  Therefore, the perimeter of triangle $AMN$ is $AM + MN + NA = 5 + 33 + 21 = \boxed{59}$.

