Let $A = (1 + 4t, 4 + 3t)$ and $B = (-5 + 4s, 6 + 3s).$  Then the vector $\overrightarrow{BA}$ is given by
\[\begin{pmatrix} 1 + 4t - (-5 + 4s) \\ 4 + 3t - (6 + 3s) \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 6 + 4t - 4s \\ -2 + 3t - 3s \end{pmatrix}.\]Let $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$ be the projection of $\overrightarrow{BA}$ onto some vector $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}$ such that $v_1 + v_2 = -7.$  Then
\[\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 6 + 4t - 4s \\ -2 + 3t - 3s \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}}{\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}} \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}.\]We can compute that
\[\begin{pmatrix} 6 + 4t - 4s \\ -2 + 3t - 3s \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = (6 + 4t - 4s) v_1 + (-2 + 3t - 3s) v_2 = (6v_1 - 2v_2) + (4tv_1 + 3tv_2) + (-4sv_1 - 3sv_2),\]and
\[\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = v_1^2 + v_2^2.\]Thus,
\[\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{(6v_1 - 2v_2) + (4tv_1 + 3tv_2) + (-4sv_1 - 3sv_2)}{v_1^2 + v_2^2} \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix}.\]Since $v_1 + v_2 = -7,$ $v_2 = -7 - v_1.$  Then
\[\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ -7 - v_1 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{(6v_1 - 2(-7 - v_1)) + (4tv_1 + 3t(-7 - v_1)) + (-4sv_1 - 3s(-7 - v_1))}{v_1^2 + (-7 - v_1)^2} \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ -7 - v_1 \end{pmatrix}.\]This simplifies to
\[\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ -7 - v_1 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{(8t - 4s + 20) v_1 + (-21t - 3s - 14)}{2v_1^2 + 98} \begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ -7 - v_1 \end{pmatrix}.\]Matching components, we get
\begin{align*}
v_1 &= \frac{(8t - 4s + 20) v_1 + (-21t - 3s - 14)}{2v_1^2 + 98}, \\
-7 - v_1 &= \frac{(8t - 4s + 20)(-7 - v_1) + (-21t - 3s - 14)}{2v_1^2 + 98}.
\end{align*}From the first equation,
\[v_1 (2v_1^2 + 98) = (8t - 4s + 20) v_1 + (-21t - 3s - 14).\]Then $2v_1^3 + 98v_1 = 8t - 4s + 20,$ so $2v_1^3 - 8t + 4s = 20 - 98v_1.$

From the second equation,
\[-7 - v_1 (2v_1^2 + 98) = (8t - 4s + 20)(-7 - v_1) + (-21t - 3s - 14).\]Then $-2v_1^3 - 98v_1 = -8t + 4s - 20,$ so $2v_1^3 - 8t + 4s = 20 + 98v_1.$  Hence, $20 - 98v_1 = 20 + 98v_1,$ so $v_1 = 0.$

Then $v_2 = -7,$ so $\begin{pmatrix} v_1 \\ v_2 \end{pmatrix} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 0 \\ -7 \end{pmatrix}}.$

