Since the line cuts the quadrilateral into two pieces of equal area, the area of triangle $ABE$ is equal to the area of trapezoid $AEDC.$  The area of triangle $ABE$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot 1 \cdot 2 = 1,\]and the area of trapezoid $AEDC$ is
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot (3 + 4) \cdot h = \frac{7}{2} h,\]where $h$ is the height of the trapezoid.

Hence, $\frac{7}{2} h = 1,$ so $h = \frac{2}{7}.$  Then $E$ is $\left( 3, \frac{2}{7} \right),$ so the coordinates of $E$ are $\boxed{\left( 3, \frac{2}{7} \right)}.$

To find the number of digits to the right of the decimal point, we need to find the decimal representation of $\frac{54317}{80000}$. We can do this by dividing $54317$ by $80000$:

$$\begin{array}{c|cccc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 6 & 7 & 9 \\
\cline{2-5}
80000 & 5 & 4 & 3 & 1 & 7 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{4} & 8 & 0 & 0 & 0 \\
\cline{2-3}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 6 & 3 & 1 & 7 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & 6 & 4 & 0 & 0 \\
\cline{3-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 2 & 1 & 7 \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 2 & 0 & 0 \\
\cline{4-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & & 1 & 7 \\
\end{array}$$

The remainder is $17$. Since the remainder is less than the divisor, we can stop here. Therefore, the decimal representation of $\frac{54317}{80000}$ is $0.6792125$. This decimal has $\boxed{7}$ digits to the right of the decimal point.

